data.chText: 激动的；兴奋的
data.enText: feeling or showing happiness and enthusiasm

data.chText: 孩子们对打开礼物感到兴奋不已。
data.enText: The children were excited about opening their presents.

data.chText: 我对有希望到国外工作着实很激动。
data.enText: I'm really excited at the prospect of working abroad.

data.chText: 不要一看到你的名字出现在出版物中就过分激动。
data.enText: Don't get too excited by the sight of your name in print.

data.chText: 入选威尔士队使他非常兴奋。
data.enText: He was very excited to be asked to play for Wales.

data.chText: 这家新餐馆没什么值得特别激动的地方。
data.enText: The new restaurant is nothing to get excited about (= not particularly good) .

data.chText: 一群激动的人聚集在她周围。
data.enText: An excited crowd of people gathered around her.

data.chText: 受刺激的；紧张不安的
data.enText: nervous or upset and unable to relax

data.chText: 有些马在车流中会受惊。
data.enText: Some horses become excited when they're in traffic.

data.chText: 性兴奋的
data.enText: feeling sexual desire

data.chText: 汽车开近时她激动地挥着手。
data.enText: She waved excitedly as the car approached.

data.text: excited ♦ ecstatic ♦ elated ♦ rapturous ♦ euphoric ♦ exhilarated ♦ on top of the world

data.chText: 以上各词均指激动、兴奋。
data.enText: These words all describe feeling or showing happiness and enthusiasm.
excited

data.chText: 指激动的、兴奋的：
data.enText: feeling or showing happiness and enthusiasm

data.chText: 孩子们对假期兴奋不已。
data.enText: The kids were excited about the holiday.
ecstatic

data.chText: 指狂喜的、热情极高的：
data.enText: very happy, excited and enthusiastic; showing this enthusiasm

data.chText: 萨莉对她的新工作高兴得发狂。
data.enText: Sally was ecstatic about her new job.
elated

data.chText: 指兴高采烈的、欢欣鼓舞的、喜气洋洋的：
data.enText: happy and excited because of sth good that has happened or will happen

data.chText: 我为成功的喜悦所鼓舞。
data.enText: I was elated with the thrill of success.
euphoric

data.chText: 指极度愉快的、兴奋的，通常持续时间较短：
data.enText: very happy and excited, but usually only for a short time

data.chText: 我兴奋的心情持久不了。
data.enText: My euphoric mood could not last.
rapturous

data.chText: 指兴高采烈的、狂喜的、热烈的：
data.enText: expressing extreme pleasure or enthusiasm

data.chText: 他受到热烈的鼓掌欢迎。
data.enText: He was greeted with rapturous applause.
exhilarated

data.chText: 尤指体育活动后高兴的、兴奋的、激动的：
data.enText: happy and excited, especially after physical activity

data.chText: 这种速度令她兴奋不已。
data.enText: She felt exhilarated with the speed.
on top of the world

data.chText: 尤指取得成绩后欢天喜地、心满意足、非常自豪：
data.enText: ( informal ) very excited or proud, especially about sth that you have achieved

data.chText: 我太满意了，我从未想过会做得如此漂亮。
data.enText: I'm on top of the world. I never expected to do so well.
to be/feel excited/ecstatic/elated/euphoric/exhilarated/on top of the world
to look/seem/sound excited/ecstatic/elated
to be excited/ecstatic/elated/euphoric about/at sth
to be excited/elated/exhilarated by sth
to be ecstatic/elated/exhilarated with sth
a(n) excited/ecstatic/elated/euphoric mood
ecstatic/rapturous applause/praise
a(n) ecstatic/rapturous welcome/reception

example: he would become emotional over nothing at all
she was worked up about all the noise

tr: (of e.g. a molecule) made reactive or more reactive
marked by uncontrolled excitement or emotion
example: a crowd of delirious baseball fans

value.def: If you are excited, you are so happy that you cannot relax, especially because you are thinking about something pleasant that is going to happen to you.

example.ex: I'm very excited about the possibility of playing for England's first team...
example.tran: 想到可能为英格兰首屈一指的球队效力，我非常兴奋。

example.ex: I was so excited when I went to sign the paperwork I could hardly write.
example.tran: 去签文件时我非常兴奋，几乎无法写字。

example.ex: ...an excited teenager on a trek through the London shops.
example.tran: 兴奋地逛遍伦敦商店的少年

gramarinfo.label: usu v-link ADJ, oft ADJ <l>about</l> n

example.ex: 'You're  coming?' he said excitedly. 'That's fantastic! That's incredible!'
example.tran: “你要来么？”他激动地说，“那太好了！简直难以置信！”

value.def: If you are excited, you are very worried or angry about something, and so you are very alert and cannot relax.

example.ex: I don't think there's any reason to get excited about inflation...
example.tran: 我认为大可不必为通货膨胀而心烦。

example.ex: Excited voices were shouting that the road was blocked by soldiers.
example.tran: 有人气愤地喊道马路被士兵封锁了。

example.ex: Larry rose excitedly to the edge of his seat, shook a fist at us and spat.
example.tran: 拉里气愤地挺直了后背，上半身前倾至座位边缘，边朝我们挥舞拳头边吐口水。

value.boxu_usage: Take care not to confuse excited and exciting.

trans: 兴奋状态；激发态；受激状态
